23 (1) The prescription drugs included in the program;
24 (2) The number of participating pharmacies, health care providers and health insurance
25 carriers;
26 (3) The number of prescription drugs dispensed through the program;
27 (4) The estimated cost savings to consumers, health insurance carriers, employers and the
28 state during the previous calendar year and to date;
29 (5) Information regarding implementation of the audit work plan and audit findings; and
30 (6) Any other information the executive office of health and human services, or other state
31 agency designated to oversee the program pursuant to this chapter, considers relevant.
